# BitMEX API Configuration
# -----------------------
# 1. API Key: Your BitMEX API key for authentication
# 2. API Secret: Your BitMEX API secret for request signing
# 3. Environment: Set to "true" for testnet, "false" for mainnet

BITMEX_API_KEY=your_api_key_here
BITMEX_API_SECRET=your_api_secret_here
BITMEX_TESTNET=true

# Environment Notes:
# - BITMEX_TESTNET=true  -> Uses testnet.bitmex.com
# - BITMEX_TESTNET=false -> Uses www.bitmex.com
# Default is testnet if not specified

# How to obtain credentials:
# 1. Log in to BitMEX
# 2. Navigate to Settings > API Keys
# 3. Generate a new API key with appropriate permissions
# 4. Copy both the API Key and Secret immediately
# 5. Store them securely in your .env file 